extends ../partials/layout.jade

block vars
  - page = 'snackbar'
  - pageTitle = 'Snackbar'

block content
  div(class="su-col-edge-1"): div(class="su-box")
    h1 Snackbar

  div(class="su-col-4"): div(class="su-box")
    p(class="su-big") <strong>Snackbar</strong> is a colorful stripe with text that hangs on top of the page. Snackbar hangs for <strong>5 seconds</strong>, but this timeout could be changed. Snackbar will not disappear if mouse is over it.
    p Snackbars are in Interaction Elements group, so they can apply <a href="colors.html#interaction">corresponding colors</a>.

    h2 Examples

    div(class="su-c"): div(class="su-ib")
      div(class="su-fl su-mr10")
        button(class="su-positive", ng-click="notify('Positive snackbar example', {color: 'positive'})") Show positive snackbar
      div(class="su-fl su-mr10")
        button(class="su-negative", ng-click="notify('Negative snackbar example', {color: 'negative'})") Show positive snackbar
      div(class="su-fl su-mr10")
        button(class="su-black", ng-click="notify('Black snackbar example that hangs on 10 seconds', {color: 'black', timeout: 10000})") Show black snackbar

    div(class="su-clear su-m20")

    p Usage example:

    pre: code(class="javascript")
      | yourApp.controller('YourController', function($scope, <strong>suSnackbar</strong>) {
      |     $scope.$on('someEvent', function() {
      |         suSnackbar.push('Positive snackbar sample', {
      |             color: "positive",
      |             timeout: 10000
      |         }, function() {
      |             console.log('Do this when snackbar will disappear');
      |         });
      |     });
      | });
